A Family Oasis: Discovering the Beauty of Ciutadella Park
Oct 2024 • Family
A beautiful green oasis in the heart of the city was the perfect escape from the bustling streets. We enjoyed strolling along the tree-lined paths.

The stunning fountain, designed by Josep Fontserè, was a highlight for our family, and we couldn't resist taking photos in front of it. The park's peaceful ambiance, punctuated by the sounds of laughter and birds, made it a delightful spot for a family picnic.

Overall, Ciutadella Park offered us a perfect blend of relaxation and adventure, making it a must-visit!

Cascada Monumental
Jul 2022 • Couples
The "Grand Cascade" was built between 1875 and 1888 under the direction of the architect Josep Fontasere. The hydraulic project for the "Cascade" was developed by the young Antonio Gaudí, and a huge number of sculptures decorating the complex were the fruit of the work of a whole team of sculptors, among which the names of such major masters as Rossend Nobas, Rafael Atche, Joan Flotats and Venancy Valmitzhana should be mentioned.
Written December 8, 2022

Majestic fountain in a beautiful park with sketchy people around
Aug 2022
This really majestic monumental fountain is set in the Parc de la Ciutadella, very close to the red brick Triumphal Arch.
Beside the fountain the park is beautiful as well, with many walking paths and boats to hire on a small central lake.
However, I deduct one star for many sketchy people around selling trinkets, drinking and smoking weed, as well homeless sleeping around.
